{"actual_usd":0.12553999999999998,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":213,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24469,"reply":"\"I don't think so.\" *I dust a little flour from my thumb and brace my hip against the worktable, the oven giving off that steady brick warmth at my side.* \"If it was only a vision, those men would've had to build their whole lives on a feeling—and feelings, bless them, are poor fence posts in a hard wind.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-threaded strand by my temple once, thinking.* \"The whole strange glory of it is that it wasn't less than flesh—it was more. Eating, speaking, wounds you could touch, a grave left empty. If Christ only rose inside their hearts, then death stayed master of the room and everybody was just trying to make peace with that. But the claim the Church keeps making is ruder and brighter than that: He actually got up.\"\n\n\"I think people do have visions. I think hearts do get changed. But those are side dishes, not the loaf.\" *I give you a small, crooked look.* \"Was there something particular that stirred the question for you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":69.376905,"run_id":"a03534d4-94fa-467c-b54c-b0b1b80173cc"}
